Package asianFlash

This package contains the objects for the asianFlash program.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AboutDialog
    This class implements a dialog in which information about the program (version, author, etc.) is displayed.
    AbstractHelpDialog
    This class implements an abstract dialog in which the program's help files can be displayed.
    AsianFlash
    This is the main class for the Asian Flash Card program.
    AsianFlashDOM
    This class contains operations required to read the AsianFlash DOM (Document-Object-Model) information from an XML file.
    AsianFlashMainFrame
    This is the main frame which will contain the Asian Flash Card program.
    CardTest
    This class implements a flash card test.
    ChangeLogDialog
    This dialog is called to display the changelog.
    ControlButtonPanel
    This class provides the control panel containing the various buttons to handle flashcards.
    GlobalKeyEventDispatcher
    This class is the Key Event Dispatcher for the program.
    InternalFlashCard
    This class provides a flash card with three logical sides.
    MainHelpDialog
    This class implements a dialog in which the application's help file is displayed.
    MainMenuBarPanel
    This class creates a panel containing a menu bar.
    ScoreBarPanel
    This class implements the panel in which card test score bar (red, green, grey) is displayed.
    ScorePanel
    This class implements a panel in which the card test scores are displayed.
    ScratchPad
    This class contains the area on which the user can draw things.
    ScratchPadDialog
    This class contains the panel on which the user can draw things.
    StatisticsDisplayDialog
    This class contains the panel used to display the statistics for the current test.
    StatisticsTable
    This class defines the statistics table.
    StatisticsTableModel
    This class contains the model for the statistics table.
    TestSetUpDialog
    This class implements a dialog used for setting up a new test.
    TextDisplayPanel
    This class implements a panel in which to display the text for each side of the card.
    UserParameters
    This class is used to encapsulate various parameters (font size, directories, etc.) that will be editable by the user and / or stored in user configuration files.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CorrectIncorrectEnum
    This enumeration is used to indicate whether the correct/incorrect button on the control button panel is set to indicate "correct" or "incorrect".
    EnumQuickKeyDefs
    This enumeration defines the different possible quick key actions.
    TestModeEnum
    This enumeration contains the different types of tests that can be run.
